Expanding on my comment:

The issue here is that the case you have written for handling the input of `3` in the `menu` method calls another method called `selectStudents`.

This is not the method containing your sub menu logic. That method you have named `studentSubMenu`. This means that if the desired behavior of a user entering `3` is them being shown the sub menu, this won&#39;t occur unless `studentSubMenu` is either called directly in the `else if (input == 3)` block, or by `selectStudents` itself.

Your logic in `menu` could look something like:

```Java
} else if (input == 3) {
    int student = selectStudents();
    studentSubMenu(student);
}
```

